annotations.title: NASA's Perseverance rover lands on Mars
NASA's Perseverance rover lands on Mars
NASA's Mars helicopter takes flight as first aircraft piloted on another planet
NASA's Mars helicopter takes flight as first aircraft piloted on another planet

content.text:
- **Perseverance Rover Landing (Feb 18, 2021):** NASA’s Perseverance rover safely landed in Mars’ Jezero Crater on Feb. 18, 2021 ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/02/18/nasa-perseverance-rover-lands-mars#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Perseverance%20rover%20successfully%20landed,of%20past%20life%20on%20Mars)), beginning a mission to search for signs of ancient life and collect Martian rock samples for eventual return to Earth ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/02/18/nasa-perseverance-rover-lands-mars#:~:text=launched%20to%20Mars%20in%20July,a%20future%20mission%2C%20slated%20for)).

- **Ingenuity Helicopter’s First Flight (Apr 19, 2021):** NASA’s Ingenuity helicopter became the first aircraft to achieve a powered, controlled flight on another planet (Mars) on April 19, 2021 ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/04/19/nasa-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-first-flight#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Ingenuity%20Mars%20helicopter%20made,collected%20data%2C%20marks%20the%20first)). The small robotic helicopter hovered briefly above the Martian surface, demonstrating that aerial exploration is possible on Mars and paving the way for future planetary exploration with flying vehicles ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/04/19/nasa-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-first-flight#:~:text=time%20a%20human,Project)).
